    "narrative": "The LawDog starting lineup for April 25th is anchored by **Cal Raleigh** (71.29) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (68.05), who represent our highest-efficiency plays. **Cal Raleigh** benefits significantly from the matchup against Liberatore, where a 10% SP skill bump and a high-leverage #2 spot in the order make him the premier play of the day. Meanwhile, **Geraldo Perdomo**\u2019s leadoff duties against M\u00e1rquez present a massive opportunity; despite the SP\u2019s moderate xERA, the tactical boost from the #1 spot and favorable conditions push him to the top tier of our roster. **Bryson Stott** (66.12) and **Jonathan Aranda** (65.18) also provide strong production, with **Bryson Stott** enjoying a healthy platoon edge and **Jonathan Aranda** thriving against Ober due to a robust 12% SP skill rating and prime spot in the batting order.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involves **Wenceel Perez**, who was our closest cut at a 44.34 efficiency score. While he remains a high-upside asset, he fell just short of the current outfield rotation because his dynamic platoon data against Singer was slightly suppressed compared to the defensive utility and park factors offered by **Gavin Sheets** and **Jung Hoo Lee**. We are closely monitoring the risk inherent in **Taylor Ward**\u2019s matchup; while his base projection is solid, facing the elite arm of Crochet drops his effective score to 59.45. Despite the 16% park boost helping him stay in the lineup, his success is highly sensitive to Crochet\u2019s dominance. Finally, while **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** faces a formidable Gausman, he retains a starting slot at 59.41, though we have factored in a -7% penalty due to his poor BvP history in limited samples. **Drew Gilbert** remains at the bottom of the active hierarchy (44.41), and any pinch-hit availability from the bench\u2014specifically from the likes of **Masyn Winn** or **Jeremiah Jackson**\u2014will be handled conservatively to protect our seasonal game caps.",
